# Docker Compose and VS Code launch

When you add a new `docker-compose*.yml` file at the workspace root (a stack this repo runs with `-f`), **in the same change** update:

**Odysseus** is a git submodule: `docker-compose.odysseus.yml` uses `include` for `odysseus/docker-compose.yml`. Do not duplicate the full stack at the root—only add the wrapper + task + launch entry. Env: `odysseus/.env` (created by `scripts/setup.sh`).

1. **`.env.<short-name>.example`** at the repo root (setup copies it to `.env.<short-name>`).

2. **`.vscode/tasks.json`** — append shell tasks:
   - `label`: `docker-compose: <short-name> up` → `bash scripts/start.sh <short-name>`
   - `label`: `docker-compose: <short-name> down` → `bash scripts/stop.sh <short-name>`
   - Same `problemMatcher`, `group`, and `presentation` as existing compose tasks.

3. **`.vscode/launch.json`** — append launch configurations:
   - **Up:** `name` `<Title> up`, `type` `docker`, `request` `launch`, `preLaunchTask` matches up task, `dockerComposeFile` `${workspaceFolder}/docker-compose.<short-name>.yml`
   - **Down:** `name` `<Title> down`, `type` `node`, `preLaunchTask` matches down task, `runtimeExecutable` `node`, `runtimeArgs` `["-e", "process.exit(0)"]`, `console` `integratedTerminal` (same pattern as **All stacks down**)

**Do not** add per-stack `up-*.sh` / `down-*.sh` files. Use `scripts/setup.sh`, `scripts/start.sh`, and `scripts/stop.sh`. Extend `scripts/common.sh` only if the stack needs special startup (see `postgres`, `odysseus` in `start.sh`). Add new default stacks to `LAB_STACKS` in `common.sh` when they belong in `start.sh all` / `stop.sh all`.

When adding a root stack, also update **`pihole/dns-hosts.conf`** per `.cursor/rules/pihole-local-dns.mdc`.

Keep JSON valid (commas between array entries).

Do **not** skip this when adding or splitting compose files: one **up** and one **down** launch profile (and tasks) per new stack file. **`stop.sh` uses `docker compose down` without `-v`** — volumes are kept.
